      "content": "When advocacy for social justice shifts away from a commitment to universal human rights and becomes a means of imposing a specific political ideology, it can indeed resemble indoctrination. The key issue at stake is whether such advocacy still respects individuals' ability to critically engage with the ideas and to express disagreements constructively. Healthy activism should encourage open-mindedness and individual critical thought, rather than shutting down differing viewpoints under the guise of protecting against harm. It is crucial for social justice movements to keep discussions inclusive and to base their activism on broadly accepted principles, rather than exclusive ideologies.",
